<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184389>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Scanning electron micrographs of the Gnathia pilosus sp. nov. A. Ventral view of male mandibles and frontal border, B. Dorsal view of male cephalosome, C. Lateral view of adult female paratype, D. Ventral view of female habitus, E. Dorsal view of P 3 larvae cephalosome, F. Ventral view of cephalosome of P 3 larva." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/184389/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184380>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Gnathia pilosus sp. nov. Male holotype, 1.9 mm (SAM A 45580). A, Full length dorsal view. B, Lateral view of cephalosome. C, Dorsal view of frontal border. D, Dorsal view of pleotelson. E, Ventral view of left pleopod with appendix masculine. Scale bars: 100 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/184380/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184381>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Gnathia pilosus sp. nov. Male holotype, 1.9 mm (SAM A 45580). A, Dorsal view of antenna 1. B, Dorsal view of antenna 2. C, Ventral view of left mandible. D, Ventral view of left maxilliped. E, Ventral view of left pylopod. Scale bars: 100 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/184381/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184382>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Gnathia pilosus sp. nov. Male holotype, 1.9 mm (SAM A 45580). A, Lateral view of pereopod 2. B, Lateral view of pereopod 3. C, Lateral view of pereopod 4. D, Lateral view of pereopod 5. E, Lateral view of pereopod 6. Scale bars: 100 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/184382/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184383>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Gnathia pilosus sp. nov. Female paratype, 2.1 mm (SAM A 45581). A, Full length dorsal view. B, Dorsal view of antenna 1. C, Dorsal view of antenna 2. D, Ventral view of right pleopod. E, Dorsal view of pleotelson. Scale bars: 100 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/184383/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184384>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Gnathia pilosus sp. nov. Female paratype, 2.1 mm (SAM A 45581). A, Ventral view of left maxilliped. B, Ventral view of left pylopod and attached oostegite. Scale bars: 100 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/184384/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184385>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Gnathia pilosus sp. nov. Female paratype, 2.1 mm (SAM A 45581). A, Lateral view of pereopod 2. B, Lateral view of pereopod 3. C, Lateral view of pereopod 4. D, Lateral view of pereopod 5. E, Lateral view of pereopod 6. Scale bars: 100 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/184385/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184386>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Gnathia pilosus sp. nov. Third-stage praniza paratype, 2.2 mm (SAM A 45581). A, Dorsal view. B, Dorsal view of antenna 1. C, Dorsal view of antenna 2. D, Ventral view of left pleopod. E, Dorsal view of pleotelson and uropods. Scale bars: 100 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/184386/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184387>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Gnathia pilosus sp. nov. Third-stage praniza paratype, 2.2 mm (SAM A 45581). A, Ventral view of mandible. B, Ventral view of paragnath. C, Ventral view of maxillule. D, Ventral view of maxilliped. E, Ventral view of gnathopod. Scale bars: 20 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/184387/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184388>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Gnathia pilosus sp. nov. Third-stage praniza paratype, 2.2 mm (SAM A 45581). A, Lateral view of pereopod 2. B, Lateral view of pereopod 3. C, Lateral view of pereopod 4. D, Lateral view of pereopod 5. E, Lateral view of pereopod 6. Scale bars: 100 μm." ;
